166    /**
167    * Compares this object with the specified object for equality based
168    * on the value of each field. All ReadablePeriod instances are accepted.
169    * <p>
170    * Note that a period of 1 day is not equal to a period of 24 hours,
171    * nor is 1 hour equal to 60 minutes. Only periods with the same amount
172    * in each field are equal.
173    * <p>
174    * This is because periods represent an abstracted definition of a time
175    * period (eg. a day may not actually be 24 hours, it might be 23 or 25
176    * at daylight savings boundary).
177    * <p>
178    * To compare the actual duration of two periods, convert both to
179    * {@link org.joda.time.Duration Duration}s, an operation that emphasises
180    * that the result may differ according to the date you choose.

182    * @param period a readable period to check against
